       <div class="row-fluid title-container">
        <div class="container">
         <h2 class="clear">
          Announcing the 2019-20 Faculty Research Projects
         </h2>
         <div class="blurb">
          <p>
           The Neubauer Collegium for Culture and Society will support seven new faculty-led collaborative research projects in the 2019-20 academic year.
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="https://neubauercollegium.uchicago.edu/news/detail/neubauer_collegium_announces_2019_20_research_projects/">
            Read more about this topic »
           </a>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="feature item ">
       <div class="background-wrapper">
        <div class="row-fluid">
         <div class="container">
          <div class="span12">
           <img alt="" src="//d3qi0qp55mx5f5.cloudfront.net/neubauercollegium/i/features/Cultures_of_protest_HOMEPAGE.jpg?mtime=1550091950" title=""/>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="row-fluid title-container">
        <div class="container">
         <h2 class="clear">
          Cultures of Protest in Contemporary Ukraine, Belarus, and Russia
         </h2>
         <div class="blurb">
          <p>
           This series of events (Feb 27-March 1) includes a film screening, a musical performance, and a roundtable discussion about the complex interconnection of culture, archival research, and politics in the region.
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="https://neubauercollegium.uchicago.edu/faculty/cultures_of_protest_in_contemporary_ukraine_belarus_and_russia/">
            Read more about this topic »
           </a>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
